cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper is concerned with modeling dynamical systems, particularly for robot navigation and planning, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of HMMs and POMDPs also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The incorporation of domain-specific information and constraints, as well as the use of real robot data, suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
